<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-015-295 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 505 149</DOCID><JOURNAL>Los Angeles Times  Nov 7 1991 v110 pD3 17 col in.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A better system to scan text into PC. (HP's ScanJet IIc and CaereCorp.'s Typing Plus Graphics) (Computer Profile) (Hardware Review)(evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>O'Reilly, Richard.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>HP's Scan Jet IIc and Caere Corp's Caere Typist Plus Graphicsscanners are reviewed.andP;  The ScanJet IIc - $2,195 for PCs and$1,995 for Apple Macintosh computers - is not cheap, but offers anAccuPage feature which, if used with Caere Corp's $995 OmniPageProfessional 2.0 scanning program, can optimize the page scanningprocess.andP;  Where the text and background contrasts may be tooslight for ScanJet's optical character recognition (OCR) to pickup, AccuPage can be used to automatically adjust the scanner'scontrast for each color blocks of text.andP;  Though ScanJet works wellwith unblemished photocopies and printed pages, it scans faxespoorly.andP;  The Typist Plus Graphics - $595 for PCs and $695 forApple Macintosh - features gray scale imaging and graphics editingsoftware, and may be an acceptable scanner.andP;  The device scanshorizontally and works well with good quality printing on whitepaper.andP;  However, with indented texts, the scanner may encountersome problems like its predecessor Caere Typist Plus.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Caere Corp. (Products)Hewlett-Packard Co. (Products).andO;Ticker:    HWP; CAER.andO;Product:   OmniPage Professional 2.0 (Scanning software) (evaluation)HP Scanjet IIc (Scanning device) (evaluation)Caere Typist Plus Graphics (Scanning device) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     Scanning devicesEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>